German Chancellor Angela Merkel met with Polish Prime Minister Mateusz Morawiecki on Friday in Berlin amid rocky relations between the neighboring countries. Although the two leaders appeared at ease during their joint press conference and emphasized their cooperation in defense and foreign policy, Merkel noted that there are still "serious differences of opinion" between Berlin and Warsaw. Read more: Is 'Polexit' in the cards? Tusk warns Poland may quit EU Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
